modules.description: Generates prime numbers using the Sieve of Eratosthenes, filters lists of integers for primes, and checks if a single integer is prime. Operates on lists and integers, with optimized performance for large ranges. Used to precompute primes for cryptographic key generation and number theory problem solving.

Generates lists of prime numbers and their factors, and checks primality for integers. It handles both small and large primes, returning results in list formats. Used for number theory computations and factorization tasks.
